{% comment %}
  section-hero — unified hero card for every page that announces a section
  or a single item.

  One component drives:
    - Index / landing pages (/qualities/, /requirements/, /approaches/,
      /standards/, /tag-*/, /dimensions/, /articles/, /how-to/)
    - Single-item detail pages (qualities/<x>, approaches/<x>, standards/<x>,
      requirements/<x> via its bespoke layout, single article)

  Section identity comes from the data-section attribute, which sets a
  CSS custom property --cat. The colour matches the home-directory rails,
  so the homepage acts as a legend for the destination section.

  Required:
    section  Color key. One of:
               qualities | requirements | approaches | standards | tag | article | how-to
    title    H1 text (plain).

  Optional:
    eyebrow_label  Small uppercase label above the title ("Quality", "Requirement", …).
                   Used on detail pages to signal the meta-class.
    eyebrow_href   Link target for the eyebrow (typically the index page).
    lede           Single paragraph of plain text shown below the title.
    chips_html     Pre-rendered HTML for the taxonomy chip row (tags, categories).
    meta           Inline metadata line (e.g. counts). HTML allowed.

  Example (index page):
    {% raw %}{% include section-hero.liquid
        section="standards"
        title="Standards"
        lede="Authoritative references that ground qualities and requirements."
        meta="<b>184</b> standards across <b>13</b> categories." %}{% endraw %}

  Example (detail page):
    {% raw %}{% capture chips %}<a class="tag" href="/tag-usable">#usable</a>{% endcapture %}
    {% include section-hero.liquid
        section="qualities"
        title=page.title
        eyebrow_label="Quality"
        eyebrow_href="/qualities/"
        chips_html=chips %}{% endraw %}
{% endcomment %}
<header class="section-hero" data-section="{{ include.section }}">
  {% if include.eyebrow_label and include.eyebrow_label != "" %}
    {% if include.eyebrow_href and include.eyebrow_href != "" %}
  <p class="section-hero__eyebrow"><a class="section-hero__eyebrow-link" href="{{ include.eyebrow_href | relative_url }}">{{ include.eyebrow_label }}</a></p>
    {% else %}
  <p class="section-hero__eyebrow">{{ include.eyebrow_label }}</p>
    {% endif %}
  {% endif %}
  <h1 class="section-hero__title">{{ include.title }}</h1>
  {% if include.lede and include.lede != "" %}<p class="section-hero__lede">{{ include.lede }}</p>{% endif %}
  {% if include.chips_html and include.chips_html != "" %}<div class="section-hero__chips">{{ include.chips_html }}</div>{% endif %}
  {% if include.meta and include.meta != "" %}<p class="section-hero__meta">{{ include.meta }}</p>{% endif %}
</header>
